# Images and media contain alternative descriptions

Images should contain an written description of what the image is showing, for example:

```html
<img src='/path-to-image/filename.png' alt='A child in a classroom sitting at a desk listening to a teacher talk' />
```

## When not to use alternative text

You do not need to provide a description when:

- the image is purely decorative, like a background pattern
- the image content is represented by adjacent real text

You should simply provide an empty alt attribute on the image element as follows: 

```html
<img src='/path-to-image/filename.png' alt='' />
```


